  {
    "user": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1753957246.696979",
    "client_msg_id": "2768496b-b703-4464-ab3f-a56d39011c3a",
    "text": "Both notebook versions hide a reference to the runtime from userspace. To make your own userspace editor and serializer you need meta programming access via the runtime. The runtime is the spreadsheet engine. Lopecode is built on that reference. \nI don't think anything was deliberately broken but the front end language semantics have changed which needed some repairs. Still not got everything working but a good chunk is unblocked. There might have been changes to the runtime I can't quite tell yet\n\n<https://github.com/observablehq/notebook-kit/discussions/20|https://github.com/observablehq/notebook-kit/discussions/20>",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1753802014.345349",
    "parent_user_id": "UBN9AFS0N",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "4gepx",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Both notebook versions hide a reference to the runtime from userspace. To make your own userspace editor and serializer you need meta programming access via the runtime. The runtime is the spreadsheet engine. Lopecode is built on that reference. \nI don't think anything was deliberately broken but the front end language semantics have changed which needed some repairs. Still not got everything working but a good chunk is unblocked. There might have been changes to the runtime I can't quite tell yet\n\n"
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
